    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter open a fifo in non-blocking read(write) mode, `:quit` will hang if there's no other writer(reader).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim -l repro.lua`: (then neovim will hang.)\n```lua\nlocal tmp = vim.fn.tempname()\nvim.system({ 'mkfifo', tmp }):wait()\nvim.uv.fs_open(tmp, 'r', -1, function() end)\n-- vim.uv.fs_open(tmp, 'w', -1, function() end)\nvim.cmd.quit()\n-- os.exit(1)\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:quit` should not hang.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1698+gaa976f0d93\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nVim has no libuv.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux arch 6.13.1-zen1-1-zen #1 ZEN SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Sun, 02 Feb 2025 01:02:11 +0000 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.39.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
